The "don't try it in production code" bit was referring to the fact that random hardware IRQs shouldn't stomp on registers, or whatever you just interrupted is going to shit itself. Nothing to do with the bit 4 stuff.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=8">ReaperSMS</a> — Wed Jul 14, 2010 8:19 pm</p><hr />
